<item>
            <title>[HBASE-1565] Support rsync-ing of data in bin scripts</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-1565</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Every developer that works with HBase ends up inevitably writing all sorts of rsync and kill scripts. These scripts usually end up failing from time to time as our system changes. I think we should maintain some of these capabilities in our bin/ scripts directly to ease the work of our users/developers.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For the record Hadoop has recently put in similar sort of stuff in bin/hadoop-daemon.sh:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
    &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; [ &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;$HADOOP_MASTER&quot;&lt;/span&gt; != &quot;&quot; ]; then
      echo rsync from $HADOOP_MASTER
      rsync -a -e ssh --delete --exclude=.svn --exclude=&apos;logs/*&apos; --exclude=&apos;contrib/hod/logs/*&apos; $HADOOP_MASTER/ &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;$HADOOP_HOME&quot;&lt;/span&gt;
    fi
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Whatever we add can be extra options, like this $HADOOP_MASTER variable above, so that the normal operation of the scripts is not affected.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
